01:07:40.170 --> 01:07:45.740 align:middle line:90%
so this is just--

01:07:45.740 --> 01:07:49.750 align:middle line:84%
so by definition, this
is symmetric, in mu nu.

01:07:49.750 --> 01:07:52.720 align:middle line:84%
This definition is
symmetric in mu nu,

01:07:52.720 --> 01:07:56.650 align:middle line:84%
because under time ordering,
you can just exchange them.

01:07:56.650 --> 01:08:00.670 align:middle line:84%
That means that in terms
of Lorentz indices,

01:08:00.670 --> 01:08:04.330 align:middle line:84%
you must be able to expand it
in some symmetric tensors built

01:08:04.330 --> 01:08:07.400 align:middle line:90%
