01:08:07.400 --> 01:08:10.420 align:middle line:84%
Because k mu is the
only vector here.

01:08:10.420 --> 01:08:13.270 align:middle line:84%
So that means you have to
build this symmetric tensor

01:08:13.270 --> 01:08:16.120 align:middle line:90%
from just eta mu mu and k mu.

01:08:16.120 --> 01:08:21.399 align:middle line:84%
And the transverse and the
longitudinal projectors

01:08:21.399 --> 01:08:25.540 align:middle line:84%
are just the tensors
you can build from k mu.

01:08:25.540 --> 01:08:26.595 align:middle line:90%
Yes?

01:08:26.595 --> 01:08:27.970 align:middle line:84%
AUDIENCE: Until
